  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of legislation and regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- Basel Committee Guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act (AMLA)\n- Patriot Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Currency Transaction Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Components\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- International information sharing\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Civil penalties\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Financial institution sanctions\n- International cooperation\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Securities and Exchange Commission\n- Internal Revenue Service\n- Department of Justice\n\n6. Compliance Requirements\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Employee training\n- Regular audits\n\nThe framework aims to prevent criminal organizations from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income.",
